## Optional: Section Grading

When the user requests grading (e.g., `/copyedit quality --grade`), provide a letter grade per section:

| Grade | Meaning |
|-------|---------|
| A | Paragraphs focused, mechanisms clear, math exact, no padding |
| A- | Minor economy issues, one paragraph slightly overloaded |
| B+ | Some inventorial numbers or missing motivation |
| B | Multiple unfocused paragraphs or hand-waved math |
| B- | Significant missing mechanisms or intellectual imprecision |
| C+ | Systematic throat-clearing or false structural framing |
| C | Fundamental issues: wrong characterization of results, missing causal logic |

Grade summary format:

```markdown
## Section Grades

| Section | Grade | Primary Issue |
|---------|-------|---------------|
| Introduction | A- | Minor throat-clearing in opening |
| Model | B+ | Two paragraphs overloaded |
| Estimation | B | Identification hand-waved in prose |
| Results | A | Clean, mechanistic, terse |
| Counterfactuals | B- | Inventorial numbers, missing mechanisms |
```

