## Relationship to Other Tasks

- **ai_detection** (Haiku): Quickly flags surface LLM patterns (punctuation, vocabulary, transitions). Part C flags rhetorical patterns but defers definitive paragraph-level judgment here.
- **writing_quality** (Sonnet): Makes the deep judgment call — is the paragraph genuinely good writing? Uses the author's standards, not just LLM pattern matching.
- **word_choice**: Handles individual word substitutions (Anglo-Saxon over Latin, weak verbs). Writing_quality handles paragraph-level quality.
- **sentence_analysis**: Handles sentence rhythm and S-V-O structure. Writing_quality handles whether the paragraph's argument is sound.

If `ai_detection` flags a pattern that `writing_quality` also addresses, `writing_quality` takes precedence in wrapup deduplication.

---

## Quality Control

- [ ] `writing_quality.md`: Assessment appended (not overwritten)
- [ ] Section header `## [filename.tex]` present
- [ ] Every flagged item has Dimension, Comment, Original, Proposed, Why better
- [ ] Priority ordering respected: intellectual precision > mechanism > structure > focus
- [ ] Proposed revisions are actionable rewrites, not vague advice
- [ ] Math precision flags include what formula should replace the prose
- [ ] No overlap with word_choice (individual word issues) or sentence_analysis (rhythm)
- [ ] `references/writing_quality_standards.md` was read before analysis
